summary: TL*THE CONTACT OWNS A 2007 SUNNYBROOK BRISTOL BAY.  THE VEHICLE HAS KENDA KARRIER LOAD STAR TIRES (NA), SIZE ST235/80/R16 (NA).  THE REAR DRIVER'S SIDE TIRE DEVELOPED A BLISTER AND WAS REPLACED.  SECONDLY, THE CONTACT NOTICED THAT THE TIRE WAS SEVERELY DEFLATED.  SEVERAL MONTHS LATER, WHILE DRIVING APPROXIMATELY 55 MPH, SHE  EXPERIENCED A DOUBLE BLOW-OUT OF THE PASSENGER REAR TIRES WITHOUT ANY WARNING.  THE CONTACT REPLACED THE TIRES AT THE COST OF $600.  SHE CALLED THE MANUFACTURER AND IS IN THE PROCESS OF FILING A WARRANTY CLAIM.  THE CONTACT HAS PICTURES OF THE FAILURE.  THE FAILURE AND CURRENT MILEAGES WERE 7,261.
